## **Simplified 2-State Design**

| State | Trigger | Behavior |
|-------|---------|----------|
| **P2P/Real-time** | Message received within last **60 seconds** | Maintain direct P2P connection, messages flow peer-to-peer |
| **Async/Polling** | No message for **60 seconds** OR P2P connection broken | Poll server every 60s for queued messages |

## **Why This Works Better:**

**Simpler Logic:**
```
if (time_since_last_message < 60s) {
    maintain_or_create_p2p_connection();
    send_direct();
} else {
    fallback_to_polling();
}
```

**No "Active" Middle State:** The 10-second polling was unnecessary complexity. Either you're actively chatting (P2P) or you're idle (async).

**Automatic Transition:** Client doesn't "choose" — it just checks last message time and acts accordingly.

**Resource Efficiency:**
- 95% of time: 60s polling (negligible load)
- 5% of time: P2P connection (brief, direct)
- Server only handles messages during idle periods

